newsitem.title: USA: CME November lumber down limit on weak cash, stops.
newsitem.headline: CME November lumber down limit on weak cash, stops.

text.p: Continued pressure from a declining cash market pushed CME lumber futures through technical support and November fell the $10.00 per tbf limit on sell stops, traders said.
November was down limit at $339.30 per tbf with other months off $7.50 to $5.20 per tbf.
Technical support on the early setback lacked followthrough and futures pushed through the chart point at $340.00 per tbf, basis November, to fall the limit, they said.
